<html><body><casebody firstpage="974" lastpage="974" xmlns="http://nrs.harvard.edu/urn-3:HLS.Libr.US_Case_Law.Schema.Case_Body:v1">
<docketnumber id="b986-6">No. 9643.</docketnumber>
<parties id="b986-7">James H. Cosgrove vs. His Creditors.</parties>
<headnotes id="b986-8">In proceedings in insolvency by a husband, where property is withheld from his schedule because his wife claims to have bought it with money given or paid her by him, the wife should he made a party, and the cause will be remanded in order that she intervene or be called in by the creditors.</headnotes>
<opinion>[NO OPINION]</opinion></casebody>
</body></html>
